name: Cybertruck explosion
summary: On January 24th, a Cybertruck exploded near the Trump International Hotel in Las Vegas, killing one person and injuring seven. The suspect, identified as a "Rambo type" with an affinity for Donald Trump, is believed to have intentionally caused the explosion. The Cybertruck was found to contain firework mortars and gas canisters. Las Vegas police are investigating potential links between this incident and a recent attack in New Orleans. The driver of the Cybertruck, who was found with a self-inflicted gunshot wound to the head, was from Colorado Springs. Law enforcement officials are considering the possibility of a terrorist motive in the explosion.

name: Tiger Bech
summary: Tragedy struck the Princeton University community and beyond when Tiger Bech, a former football player and 2021 graduate, lost his life in a terror attack on Bourbon Street in New Orleans. Bech, described as "so beautiful and full of life," was among the victims alongside the brother of TCU football player Jack Bech. The New York City stockbroker and former Princeton footballer succumbed to injuries sustained during the horrific incident. The Princeton Football team, along with various news outlets and organizations, mourned Bech's passing and paid tribute to his memory. The attack also claimed the lives of other innocent individuals, leaving behind a trail of grief and unanswered questions.
